HealthAI — Calorie Counter
Free text → kcal. Powered by spaCy NER.
Setup
bashpip install spacy
python -m spacy download en_core_web_sm
Train the NER model (once)
bashpython nlp/train_ner.py
Generates nlp/food_ner_model/ — the trained model.
Without it, falls back to regex automatically.
Run
bashpython test.py        # interactive
python test.py --test # batch examples
Use in FastAPI
pythonfrom analyze import analyze

result = analyze("2 eggs and a banana")
print(result.total_kcal)   # 307.0
print(result.items)        # [{"food": "egg", "grams": 120, "kcal": 186}, ...]
print(result.message)      # "This meal contains approximately 307 kcal."
Structure
ai_simple/
├── data/
│   ├── nutrition_data.py      # loads kaggle_nutrition.csv
│   └── kaggle_nutrition.csv   # ← put your Kaggle CSV here
├── nlp/
│   ├── parser.py              # spaCy NER + regex fallback
│   ├── train_ner.py           # training script
│   └── food_ner_model/        # generated after training
├── analyze.py                 # main interface
├── test.py
└── requirements.txt